          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You absolutely can learn to trust yourself. Everyone has this capacity - it's not special or reserved for religious people or experts. But like any skill, it requires practice. Start by noticing small signals and acting on them in low-risk ways - encouraging a friend, warning someone gently, sharing what you sense with someone you trust. Watch what happens. Over time, you'll build real confidence in your own ability to recognize what's true. You don't need permission from anyone else to know your own life and what you're sensing in it."
